         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">22/3/78 ¶ Strictly Private ¶  ¶ I need not assure you, dear Mr Ramsay, that I will be happy to support your candidature at the R.S., ¶  but this months mail is gone. So perhaps you will advise me to w...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">78.03.22</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Edward Ramsay</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">ML MSS.562, Letters to E. P. Ramsay 1862-91, Mitchell Library, State Library of New South Wales, Sydney.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, '﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽ Symbol'; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">22/3/78</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, '﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽ Symbol'; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Strictly Private</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, '﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽ Symbol'; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I need not assure you, dear Mr Ramsay, that I will be happy to support your candidature at the R.S.,<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, '﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽ Symbol'; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Royal Society, London. Ramsay was never nominated for election to the Society (see Home (2003)).</p>
               </note> but this months mail is gone. So perhaps you will advise me to whom to write. I will gladly write to our venerable friend Prof. Owen, who will likely be the next president,<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, '﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽ Symbol'; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Owen was never President of the Royal Society.</p>
               </note> and if Lord Lewis's adress is given me,<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, '﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽ Symbol'; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Not identified. There was no Fellow of the Royal Society with this surname in 1878.</p>
               </note> I will readily communicate with him also.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, '﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽ Symbol'; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>There is plenty of time till next mail. Can you confidentially give me some clue to the <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">real</hi>
               </seg> feelings of Moore towards me? How is it, that he instead of bravely supporting my Directorship so <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">eagerly</hi>
               </seg> recommends that I should <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">accept</hi>
               </seg> the change, when I had nothing to accept, but was simply deprived homeless of my whole Department and thus thrown into abject poverty? How is that Mr Francis,<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, '﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽ Symbol'; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>James Francis.</p>
               </note> after seeing mere lawns and not even a glass-house (for £8000 a year there) at your Garden, so soon as he came back in 1873 from the Sydney conference, resolved, that there "must be here a change".<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, '﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽ Symbol'; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     </seg>See C. Moore to J. Hooker 24 February 1873 (in this edition as M73-02-24).</p>
               </note> I never shall forget <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">that</hi>
               </seg>! Mr M. has promised me plants from Lord Howes Isl; but none have come for months;<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, '﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽ Symbol'; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     </seg>See C. Moore to G. Bentham, 19 February 1876 (in this edition as M76-02-19).</p>
               </note> he also tells me, that I shall have a set of his N. Guinea plants; perhaps his collector is not yet back.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, '﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽ Symbol'; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>My own impression is, that at least cautiously &amp; <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">indirectly</hi>
               </seg> he has contributed after all my generosity to him as much to my ruin &amp; deep sadness &amp; distress, as the man in Adelaide.<note xml:id="ftn7" type="footnote" n="7">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, '﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽ Symbol'; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Richard Schomburgk.</p>
               </note> Is jealousy the spring of this like at Kew? Hooker gives [me pur]posely<note xml:id="ftn8" type="footnote" n="8">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, '﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽ Symbol'; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Paper damaged.</p>
               </note> &amp; studiously <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">no support</hi>
               </seg> though (except Owen) all men of science rallied round him against Ayrton.<note xml:id="ftn9" type="footnote" n="9">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, '﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽ Symbol'; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See MacLeod (1974).</p>
               </note> H. wants merely <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">collectors</hi>
               </seg> at the Colonial establishments &amp; Kew is to monopolize all of British wri[ting]<note xml:id="ftn10" type="footnote" n="10">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, '﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽ Symbol'; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Word partly illegible. There is no signature, suggesting that at least one page of the letter is missing.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
         </div>
      </body>
